{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847990463,"sessionID":"ses_28737182bfferMscz6UMoo0a4N","part":{"id":"prt_d78c95f42001cw6f3NbAQUeplp","messageID":"msg_d78c93e63001snPbExIURq2hQh","sessionID":"ses_28737182bfferMscz6UMoo0a4N","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_8da03cbd0af04508a059962c","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n\n## Context\n\nModule: `cmd`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: M\n\nThe agentcube project requires 4 CLI binary entry points under `cmd/`. Currently `cmd/agentd` and `cmd/picod` exist. This delta adds `cmd/workloadmanager` and `cmd/router`, and standardizes all 4 binaries with consistent flag parsing, logging, and graceful shutdown.\n\n## Existing binaries\n\n| Binary | Package | Role |\n|--------|---------|------|\n| `agentd` | `pkg/agentd` | Sandbox controller (controller-runtime) |\n| `picod` | `pkg/picod` | Pico code-interpreter server |\n\n## New binaries\n\n| Binary | Package | Role |\n|--------|---------|------|\n| `workloadmanager` | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Workload manager — reconciles AgentRuntime & CodeInterpreter CRs |\n| `router` | `pkg/router` | API router/gateway — reverse proxy with JWT auth & load balancing |\n\n## Decisions\n\n- All binaries use `k8s.io/klog/v2` for logging (consistent with `picod`).\n- All binaries accept `--kubeconfig` and `--master` flags for Kubernetes connectivity.\n- All binaries support graceful shutdown via `ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()`.\n- `agentd` retains controller-runtime logger (`zap`) for compatibility with existing reconciler.\n- Build targets are defined via `go build ./cmd/<binary>`.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CLI-01 — `agentd` binary standardization\n\n**Given** the `cmd/agentd/main.go` entry point exists  \n**When** a user runs `agentd --help`  \n**Then** the binary prints usage including `--kubeconfig`, `--master`, and zap logger flags\n\n**Given** the `agentd` binary is running  \n**When** a SIGTERM signal is received  \n**Then** the manager stops gracefully and exits with code 0\n\n**Given** an invalid kubeconfig is provided  \n**When** the `agentd` binary starts  \n**Then** it logs the error and exits with code 1\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CLI-02 — `picod` binary standardization\n\n**Given** the `cmd/picod/main.go` entry point exists  \n**When** a user runs `picod --help`  \n**Then** the binary prints usage including all server configuration flags (port, auth, etc.)\n\n**Given** the `picod` binary is running  \n**When** a SIGTERM signal is received  \n**Then** the HTTP server shuts down gracefully and exits with code 0\n\n**Given** the configured port is already in use  \n**When** the `picod` binary starts  \n**Then** it logs the error and exits with code 1\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CLI-03 — `workloadmanager` binary\n\n**Given** the `pkg/workloadmanager` package exists with reconciler and handler logic  \n**When** a developer creates `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`  \n**Then** the binary initializes a Kubernetes clientset using `client-go` (not controller-runtime)\n\n**Given** the `workloadmanager` binary starts  \n**When** `--kubeconfig` and `--master` flags are parsed  \n**Then** it builds a `rest.Config` and creates a `Clientset` from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n\n**Given** the `workloadmanager` binary is configured  \n**When** it initializes the informer factory  \n**Then** it starts `SharedInformerFactory` for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` types\n\n**Given** the `workloadmanager` binary is running  \n**When** a SIGTERM signal is received  \n**Then** the informer factory calls `Shutdown()` and the binary exits with code 0\n\n**Given** the `workloadmanager` binary starts  \n**When** the reconciler is initialized  \n**Then** it registers event handlers for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` informers\n\n**Given** a user runs `workloadmanager --help`  \n**Then** the output includes `--kubeconfig`, `--master`, `--workers` (reconciler concurrency), and `--resync-period` flags\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CLI-04 — `router` binary\n\n**Given** the `pkg/router` package exists with HTTP server, JWT middleware, and load balancer  \n**When** a developer creates `cmd/router/main.go`  \n**Then** the binary initializes the router server with configurable options\n\n**Given** the `router` binary starts  \n**When** flags are parsed  \n**Then** it accepts `--listen-addr`, `--kubeconfig`, `--master`, `--jwt-secret`, and `--resync-period` flags\n\n**Given** the `router` binary is configured  \n**When** it initializes informers  \n**Then** it uses the `SharedInformerFactory` to watch `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources for backend discovery\n\n**Given** the `router` binary is running  \n**When** a SIGTERM signal is received  \n**Then** the HTTP server performs graceful shutdown with a configurable timeout and exits with code 0\n\n**Given** the `--jwt-secret` flag is not provided  \n**When** the `router` binary starts  \n**Then** it logs a warning and runs without JWT authentication (dev mode)\n\n**Given** a user runs `router --help`  \n**Then** the output includes all server and Kubernetes connection flags\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CLI-05 — Build targets\n\n**Given** the project root contains `go.mod`  \n**When** a developer runs `go build ./cmd/agentd`  \n**Then** the `agentd` binary is produced in the current directory\n\n**Given** the project root contains `go.mod`  \n**When** a developer runs `go build ./cmd/picod`  \n**Then** the `picod` binary is produced in the current directory\n\n**Given** the project root contains `go.mod`  \n**When** a developer runs `go build ./cmd/workloadmanager`  \n**Then** the `workloadmanager` binary is produced in the current directory\n\n**Given** the project root contains `go.mod`  \n**When** a developer runs `go build ./cmd/router`  \n**Then** the `router` binary is produced in the current directory\n\n**Given** all 4 cmd packages compile  \n**When** `go build ./cmd/...` is run  \n**Then** all 4 binaries are built without errors\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CLI-06 — Version flag (all binaries)\n\n**Given** any of the 4 binaries is built  \n**When** the binary is invoked with `--version`  \n**Then** it prints the module version from build-time ldflags (or `devel` if not set) and exits with code 0\n\n---\n\n## File changes\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` | Create | CLI entry point for workload manager |\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | Create | CLI entry point for router/gateway |\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Modify | Add `--kubeconfig`, `--master` flags; signal handling |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | Modify | Add signal handling for graceful shutdown |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775847990455,"end":1775847990461}}}}
