{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848082968,"sessionID":"ses_28737182bfferMscz6UMoo0a4N","part":{"id":"prt_d78ca7e43001WAkSAwRafbijc1","messageID":"msg_d78ca632f001uuiwwML8a6GJ8N","sessionID":"ses_28737182bfferMscz6UMoo0a4N","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_5e939c5b858a449da693b6bf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `agentd` binary — existing entry point\n\nThe `cmd/agentd/main.go` binary SHALL remain as the Sandbox controller using controller-runtime. The binary SHALL accept `--kubeconfig` and `--master` flags for out-of-cluster Kubernetes connectivity.\n\n#### Scenario: agentd starts with in-cluster config\n\n- **GIVEN** the binary runs inside a Kubernetes pod with a valid service account\n- **WHEN** `agentd` is invoked without `--kubeconfig` or `--master`\n- **THEN** it uses `ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()` to obtain in-cluster config and starts the manager\n\n#### Scenario: agentd starts with out-of-cluster config\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file exists at `/path/to/kubeconfig`\n- **WHEN** `agentd --kubeconfig=/path/to/kubeconfig` is invoked\n- **THEN** it loads the kubeconfig and starts the manager\n\n#### Scenario: agentd graceful shutdown\n\n- **GIVEN** the `agentd` binary is running\n- **WHEN** a SIGTERM signal is received\n- **THEN** `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())` returns and the process exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario: agentd fails on invalid config\n\n- **GIVEN** `--kubeconfig` points to a non-existent file\n- **WHEN** `agentd` is invoked\n- **THEN** it logs the error to `setupLog` and exits with code 1\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: `picod` binary — existing entry point\n\nThe `cmd/picod/main.go` binary SHALL remain as the Pico code-interpreter server. The binary SHALL use `picod.ParseFlags()` for configuration and `server.Run()` for execution with signal handling.\n\n#### Scenario: picod starts with default config\n\n- **GIVEN** no flags are provided\n- **WHEN** `picod` is invoked\n- **THEN** `ParseFlags()` returns a config with defaults and `server.Run()` starts the HTTP server\n\n#### Scenario: picod graceful shutdown\n\n- **GIVEN** the `picod` binary is running (via `server.Run()`)\n- **WHEN** a SIGTERM signal is received\n- **THEN** the HTTP server shuts down gracefully and the process exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario: picod fails on port conflict\n\n- **GIVEN** the configured port is already bound by another process\n- **WHEN** `picod` is invoked\n- **THEN** `server.Run()` logs the error via `klog.Fatalf` and the process exits with code 1\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: `workloadmanager` binary — new entry point\n\nA new binary SHALL be created at `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`. The binary SHALL initialize the `SandboxReconciler` from `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler` and run it with the provided configuration.\n\nThe binary SHALL:\n\n1. Parse CLI flags: `--kubeconfig`, `--master`, `--workers`, `--resync-period`, `--store-type`\n2. Build a `rest.Config` for Kubernetes connectivity\n3. Create a `clientset.Interface` from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset`\n4. Create a `SharedInformerFactory` with the configured resync period\n5. Create listers for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter`\n6. Optionally create a Pod informer (if `--watch-pods` is true)\n7. Initialize the store client via `pkg/store`\n8. Construct `ReconcilerDeps` and create `SandboxReconciler`\n9. Call `reconciler.Run(stopCh)` with signal handler\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager starts with in-cluster config\n\n- **GIVEN** the binary runs inside a Kubernetes pod\n- **WHEN** `workloadmanager` is invoked without `--kubeconfig`\n- **THEN** it uses `rest.InClusterConfig()` and creates a clientset\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager starts with out-of-cluster config\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file exists\n- **WHEN** `workloadmanager --kubeconfig=/path/to/kubeconfig --master=https://api.example.com` is invoked\n- **THEN** it builds a `rest.Config` from the flags and creates a clientset\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager initializes informers\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid clientset is created\n- **WHEN** the binary constructs the `SharedInformerFactory`\n- **THEN** the factory is created with the `--resync-period` duration (default: 30s)\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager constructs reconciler\n\n- **GIVEN** all dependencies are initialized (clientset, informer factory, listers, store)\n- **WHEN** `NewSandboxReconciler(deps)` is called\n- **THEN** the reconciler is created with the specified `--workers` count (default: 2)\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager runs reconciler\n\n- **GIVEN** the reconciler is constructed\n- **WHEN** `reconciler.Run(stopCh)` is called\n- **THEN** the informer factory starts, cache syncs, and worker goroutines begin processing\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager graceful shutdown\n\n- **GIVEN** the `workloadmanager` binary is running\n- **WHEN** a SIGTERM signal is received\n- **THEN** `reconciler.Run` closes `stopCh`, the factory shuts down, the workqueue drains, and the process exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager cache sync timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** the API server is unreachable\n- **WHEN** `reconciler.Run` waits for cache sync\n- **THEN** after `cacheSyncTimeout` (30s) the reconciler logs the failure and exits with code 1\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager missing store\n\n- **GIVEN** `--store-type` is not set and no default store is available\n- **WHEN** the binary attempts to initialize the store\n- **THEN** it panics with \"Store is required\" (as enforced by `NewSandboxReconciler`)\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager help output\n\n- **GIVEN** the binary is compiled\n- **WHEN** `workloadmanager --help` is invoked\n- **THEN** the output includes `--kubeconfig`, `--master`, `--workers`, `--resync-period`, `--store-type`, and `--watch-pods` flags\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: `router` binary — new entry point\n\nA new binary SHALL be created at `cmd/router/main.go`. The binary SHALL initialize the `Server` from `pkg/router` and run it with the provided configuration.\n\nThe binary SHALL:\n\n1. Parse CLI flags: `--port`, `--debug`, `--enable-tls`, `--tls-cert`, `--tls-key`, `--max-concurrent`, `--session-check-interval`, `--session-idle-timeout`, `--session-max-duration`, `--store-type`, `--jwt-expiration`, `--jwt-issuer`, `--jwt-leeway`, `--kubeconfig`, `--master`\n2. Build a `*router.Config` from flags\n3. Call `router.NewServer(config)` to construct the server\n4. Call `server.Run()` which handles signal-based graceful shutdown internally\n\n#### Scenario: router starts with default config\n\n- **GIVEN** no flags are provided\n- **WHEN** `router` is invoked\n- **THEN** `NewDefaultConfig()` values are used and the server starts on port 8080\n\n#### Scenario: router starts with custom port\n\n- **GIVEN** `--port=9090` is provided\n- **WHEN** `router` is invoked\n- **THEN** the server listens on `:9090`\n\n#### Scenario: router starts with TLS enabled\n\n- **GIVEN** `--enable-tls --tls-cert=/path/cert.pem --tls-key=/path/key.pem` are provided\n- **WHEN** `router` is invoked\n- **THEN** the server starts HTTPS using `ListenAndServeTLS`\n\n#### Scenario: router TLS enabled but missing cert/key\n\n- **GIVEN** `--enable-tls` is provided but `--tls-cert` or `--tls-key` is empty\n- **WHEN** `router` is invoked\n- **THEN** `server.Start()` returns nil (no-op) and the process exits without starting a server\n\n#### Scenario: router graceful shutdown\n\n- **GIVEN** the `router` binary is running (via `server.Run()`)\n- **WHEN** a SIGTERM signal is received\n- **THEN** `server.Shutdown(ctx)` is called with a 10s timeout and the process exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario: router JWT key initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** the server is constructed\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config)` runs\n- **THEN** `jwtManager.TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` is called to initialize or load the JWT signing key\n\n#### Scenario: router fails on JWT initialization error\n\n- **GIVEN** the store is unreachable during JWT key loading\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config)` is called\n- **THEN** it returns an error and the binary exits with code 1\n\n#### Scenario: router fails on session manager error\n\n- **GIVEN** the store client cannot create a session manager\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config)` is called\n- **THEN** it returns an error and the binary exits with code 1\n\n#### Scenario: router help output\n\n- **GIVEN** the binary is compiled\n- **WHEN** `router --help` is invoked\n- **THEN** the output includes `--port`, `--debug`, `--enable-tls`, `--tls-cert`, `--tls-key`, `--max-concurrent`, `--store-type`, and JWT-related flags\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build targets\n\nAll 4 binaries SHALL be buildable from the module root.\n\n#### Scenario: build agentd\n\n- **GIVEN** the module root contains valid `go.mod`\n- **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/agentd` is run\n- **THEN** the `agentd` binary is produced with exit code 0\n\n#### Scenario: build picod\n\n- **GIVEN** the module root contains valid `go.mod`\n- **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/picod` is run\n- **THEN** the `picod` binary is produced with exit code 0\n\n#### Scenario: build workloadmanager\n\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` exists with valid Go code\n- **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/workloadmanager` is run\n- **THEN** the `workloadmanager` binary is produced with exit code 0\n\n#### Scenario: build router\n\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go` exists with valid Go code\n- **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/router` is run\n- **THEN** the `router` binary is produced with exit code 0\n\n#### Scenario: build all binaries\n\n- **GIVEN** all 4 cmd packages compile\n- **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/...` is run\n- **THEN** all 4 binaries are built without errors\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Code quality gates\n\nThe codebase SHALL pass the following checks after AR-019 implementation:\n\n- `go vet ./cmd/...` produces no warnings\n- `go build ./cmd/...` succeeds\n- `go mod tidy` results in no changes\n\n#### Scenario: go vet clean\n\n- **GIVEN** AR-019 is implemented\n- **WHEN** `go vet ./cmd/...` is run\n- **THEN** no warnings or errors are reported\n\n#### Scenario: all binaries build\n\n- **GIVEN** AR-019 is implemented\n- **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/...` is run\n- **THEN** exit code is 0\n\n#### Scenario: no unused dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** AR-019 is implemented\n- **WHEN** `go mod tidy` is run\n- **THEN** `go.mod` and `go.sum` are unchanged\n\n---\n\n## File changes\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` | Create | CLI entry point for workload manager reconciler |\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | Create | CLI entry point for router/gateway server |\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | No change | Existing entry point (already functional) |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | No change | Existing entry point (already functional) |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime.go\">\nERROR [51:25] undefined: LabelSessionID\nERROR [77:29] undefined: LabelSandboxName\nERROR [78:29] undefined: LabelWorkloadName\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go\">\nERROR [11:2] \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\" imported as metav1 and not used\nERROR [32:25] undefined: LabelSessionID\nERROR [58:29] undefined: LabelSandboxName\nERROR [59:29] undefined: LabelWorkloadName\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics